At the start of this year they re-introduced the license for fireworks. I think it's ridiculous. It's basically because the police can't stop people from firing them at their cars. They also claim its because of public disorder, yet I doubt that is specific to N Ireland.<br>
The license costs £30, and you must get an application from the N Ireland Office, and send it in months in advance before you can get a certificate to buy fireworks.<br>
<br>
There is also the case that too many young people throw bangers around. It's not a local problem either. These bangers are illegal, generally imported from France or Spain when people came back from their holidays. Alot are not even legal in France and are dangerous. The police will be able to stop anyone who lets off a firework, and it will make them more aware of the illegal ones. Yet how it is going to be policed I don't know!<br>
<br>
I wouldn't pay £30 for the small fireworks display we have every year. I think it's absolutely stupid, and they should work on fighting against the riots, and stopping the people in them (bring on the zero tolerance) instead of ruining innocent parties.<br>
<br>
I am sure you can get dodgy ones, and I am sure it's very hard to get caught too! but the whole thing is not needed, and I don't think it helps work towards peace like some might.<br>
<br>
There are also huge police shortages here, because of riots and stuff like that. We have the biggest amount of officers off work (on the sick) in the UK.<br>
<br>
Would you bother to get a license if you had these silly rules?<br>
<br>
Would you consider buying dodgy fireworks? (as in illegal, not the ones that shoot in 100 directions blinding you)<br>
<br>
Do you honestly think it will stop these huge crowds of rioters from firing them at the police? (noting that they don't catch the majority of the people involved!) <p></p><span class=m><i></i></span><hr size=1>   &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbbardenfrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/reply.gif border=0 width=20 height=20 alt="reply to this message" align=absmiddle></a>   <br><br></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCE6FF><td colspan=2><table cellpadding=8 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td nowrap width=20% valign=top><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bbbarden.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=swallow>Swallow</A> </span><br><br> <span class=usertitle>Deep Blue Sea<br /><img src=http://www.bbarden.com/img/levels/userlevel-2-4.gif /></span><br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m width=80%><span class=m><font color=#FF0000>Posted: 10/4/02 10:07:45 pm</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br><span class=title> -</span><hr size=1> Seems like they have their priorities wrong. It won't stop the crowd- there are alway 'ways' to get hold of stuff like that.  <p></p><span class=m><i></i></span><hr size=1>   &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbbardenfrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=1><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/reply.gif border=0 width=20 height=20 alt="reply to this message" align=absmiddle></a>   <br><br></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td colspan=2><table cellpadding=8 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td nowrap width=20% valign=top><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/uconfound.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CoNfOuNd</A> </span><br><BR><img src=http://peter.armo.co.uk/img/irish.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60><br> <span class=usertitle>Createur de Projets<br /><img src='http://www.bbarden.com/img/levels/userlevel-admin.gif' /><br /><img src='http://www.bbarden